#### Origin of Uphrust

Uphrust is the net upward force exerted by a fluid on a body because of the body being immersed (either partially or totally) in the fluid.

Uphrust arises because fluid pressure increases directly proportionally with depth in the fluid. Thus, the pressure at the lower part of a body is higher than the pressure at the upper part of the body. This pressure differences results in the sum of the upward force components due to the fluid pressure to be greater in magnitude than the sum of the downward force components due to the fluid pressure. Hence a net upward force is exerted by the fluid on the body, which is known as upthrust.

